<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="74" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="74">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="74">
The genus 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Oonopidae" genus="Aposphragisma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aposphragisma" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Aposphragisma</taxonomicName>
most resembles the genera 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Oonopidae" genus="Gamasomorpha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gamasomorpha" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Gamasomorpha</taxonomicName>
Karsch, 1881 and 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Oonopidae" genus="Xestaspis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xestaspis" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Xestaspis</taxonomicName>
Simon, 1884 (
<bibRefCitation author="Thoma, M" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="14" pageNumber="85" pagination="1 - 86" title="The new Southeast Asian goblin spider genus Aposphragisma (Araneae, Oonopidae): diversity and phylogeny." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3798.1.1" volume="3798" year="2014">Thoma et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
) but they can be differentiated based on the combination of the following characters: hard-bodied spiders; sternum with microsculpture; dorsal and ventral abdominal scuta not fused; labium strongly incised; legs without spines. Furthermore, males are distinguished by their palpal bulb bearing an apical embolus closely associated with a laminar conductor (
<bibRefCitation author="Thoma, M" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="14" pageNumber="85" pagination="1 - 86" title="The new Southeast Asian goblin spider genus Aposphragisma (Araneae, Oonopidae): diversity and phylogeny." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3798.1.1" volume="3798" year="2014">Thoma et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="74" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="74">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="74">Borneo, Indonesia (Sumatra), Malaysia, Singapore and Vietnam.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
